Description

zkArena Quest is a Game + NFT Entertainment platform that combines mini-game tournament elements with character and item NFTs.
Players can compete in web-based games, collect exclusive NFTs, and exchange rewards across chains.
The Soundness Layer is used to:

Verify game scores with Zero-Knowledge Proofs to prevent cheating.

Ensure transparent distribution of NFT/token rewards while maintaining player data privacy.

SL Integration

The game client sends match results to the backend, where the backend generates a zk-proof of valid results.

Proof is verified by a smart contract on the Soundness Layer + Sui to determine rewards.

Only proofs are stored on-chain (not full score details) → privacy + gas savings.

NFTs drop directly on-chain based on valid results.

Technical

Architecture

Frontend (Game Client): React + Phaser.js (web game)
Backend: Node.js (verify score results & generate zk-proof)
Blockchain: Sui + Soundness Layer
NFT: Characters, skins, items (Mint via smart contract after proof is valid)

Flow:

1. Player plays → score results

2. Backend calculates score & generates zk-proof of validity

3. Proof is sent to smart contract

4. Contract verifies proof via Soundness Layer

5. If valid → player receives NFT/reward

